  "prompt": "Why do I constantly search for and look at pictures of my ex and his new girlfriend? What is going on in my mind?",
  "response": "It's completely normal to have lingering feelings and thoughts after a significant relationship ends, especially if your ex is now with someone new. Here are some possible reasons for your behavior:\n\n**1. Emotional Closure:** You might be searching for a sense of closure. Looking at pictures of your ex with his new girlfriend could be a way to process the change and come to terms with the end of the relationship.\n\n**2. Curiosity:** It's natural to feel curious about your ex's new life. You might be wondering about his new relationship and comparing yourself to his new partner to understand why things didn't work out between you two.\n\n**3. Residual Feelings:** This behavior could be a sign that you still have unresolved feelings for your ex. You might be struggling to let go and move on.\n\n**4. Self-Esteem:** Looking at pictures might be a way of unconsciously protecting your self-esteem. If you see your ex happy with someone else, it could challenge your self-worth and make you question your value.\n\n**5. Habit:** After a breakup, people often fall into certain habits that can be hard to break. If you were used to checking up on your ex during the relationship, this behavior might persist even after the breakup.\n\nIt can be helpful to reflect on your feelings and motivations behind this behavior. Consider talking to a trusted friend or therapist for support in understanding and navigating your emotions during this time. Working on self-care and focusing on your own growth and interests can also help you move forward.",
